---
title: Ginger, Lime and Garlic Chicken Stew with Spinach and Basmati Rice
description: Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Ginger, Lime and Garlic Chicken Stew in just 20 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/HF220824_R12_W40_UK_G3924-11328-6_KB_Main_low-053026d5.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/ginger-lime-and-garlic-chicken-stew-63b56f01749d7fa20bf99a17-c8a7870c.pdf
cuisine: Fusion
nutrition:
  calories: 691 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 20.3 g
  carbohydrates: 75.5 g
  sugar: 7.4 g
  protein: 43.7 g
  sodium: 3.3 g
  serving size: 388
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/ginger-lime-and-garlic-chicken-stew-63b56f01749d7fa20bf99a17
author: Mimi Morley
time required: 20 minutes
---

Boil a full #kettle{}.

While it boils, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked
through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}.

Once the water has boiled, pour into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{0.25%tsp}
on high heat.

Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back into the pan. Cover with a #lid{}
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Once the chicken is cooked, stir in the garlic, @ginger puree{15%g} and
@tomato puree{30%g}. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @sugar for the
sauce{1} and @water for the sauce{75%ml}, then stir together.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the sauce has
thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once thickened, stir in the @baby spinach{40%g} into the stew a handful at a
time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from the heat, squeeze in some of the lime juice and stir in the
@soy sauce{15%ml}.

Taste and add more lime if needed and add a splash more water if it's a bit too
thick.

Share the rice between your #bowls{} and spoon the chicken stew on top.

Finish with a sprinkling of lime zest.

Enjoy!